div.p:
The third reaſon is this: If grace

may be wholly loſt, then no man can bee aſſured of his ſaluation, neither can haue peace with God, nor pray in faith without doubting: but the faithfull man is certaine of his ſaluation, otherwiſe hee hath not faith, becauſe certaintie is of the nature of faith;
Certitude eſt de natura fidei. and hath peace with God, Rom. 5.1; and prayeth in faith without wauering, Iam. 1.6. Ergo.
